description:
Doggy Bag is a Read it Later client for webOS 3.x.  Using Doggy Bag and Read It Later, you can save links to web pages to read later when you have time.  There are many ways to add items to your Read It Later list.  You can use Doggy Bag itself, an extension for one of the many popular desktop web browsers, a plugin for Google Reader, or use integration with several existing webOS apps.  Alternatively, using Doggy Bag and Read It Later provides an easy way to share links from any computer or phone for viewing on your webOS device.

Doggy Bag not only allows you to view items in your Read It Later list, but it makes it easy to manage your queue as list.  Upon viewing an item, you can mark it as having been “read”, or mark an item that has already been read as “unread”.  It is also very easy to add a page to your list by simply supplying the address and a name for which to remember the page.

Support, feedback and suggestions are welcome at support@yellowfinsolutions.com

Doggy Bag requires a Read It Later account.  Read It Later is a free service to use.  Doggy Bag stores an encrypted version of your user name and password on your device, but does not transmit or share this information with anyone, including the developer.
